لائیو اسکرپٹ کا نام بدل کر جاوا اسکرپٹ ر: Was LiveScript renamed to JavaScript? LiveScript JavaScript rename history
JavaScript was originally named Mocha, later it was renamed to LiveScript, and then to JavaScript. The LiveScript to JavaScript name change came because Netscape and Sun did a license agreement.
Was LiveScript renamed to JavaScript? LiveScript JavaScript rename history

JavaScript was originally developed by Brendan Eich of Netscape Communications Corporation under the name Mocha, then LiveScript, and finally renamed to JavaScript. The change of name from LiveScript to JavaScript roughly coincided with Netscape adding support for Java technology in its Netscape Navigator web browser.
